KANO – Air passengers on Tuesday staged a peaceful protest in front of the Azman Air office over sudden cancellations of booked flights to Lagos. The passengers who were mainly identified as members of the Kano House of Assembly vent their anger at what they described as “unfair treatment”. Bashir Abdullahi, one of the affected passengers, told DAILY INDEPENDENT at the scene of the protest that he was travelling to Egypt en route Lagos on a scheduled flight tomorrow as he lamented that the untoward action by the airline would visit on him serious consequences. Obasa, Lagos Speaker, To Chair Anchor University Lecture… Lukman’s Forced Resignation Retrogressive — APC Rebirth Tells… Abdullahi said, “Actually, I don’t know what to do next, because I have budgeted for everything about my trip, but look at what this Azman did to us.” At the time of the protest, there was no top management staff around to respond to the emergency, but one Bashir Otara who identified himself as the chief security officer to the airline said the hiccups was necessitated by “technical malfunctions “. He, therefore, called for calm that the management was doing its best to address the problems in due course. Details soon…